❯ what lights are in our level?                                                 

  Called thirdperson-game-iq 12 times (ctrl+o to expand)

● Confirmed: NewMap (the project's main World Partition level) has only 3
  directly-indexed actors — WorldSettings, Brush, WorldDataLayers. No lights are
  indexed there because World Partition stores actors as external actor
  packages, which this index doesn't currently resolve into typed level-actor
  entities (unlike the two non-WP Niagara sample levels).

  The GameIQ index does have full light data for two other levels in the project
  (both Niagara plugin sample content, not likely "our" gameplay level):

  GalleryLevel (/Game/NiagaraExamples/GalleryLevel):
  - SunLight — DirectionalLight, intensity 8, white, Movable
  - MoonLight — DirectionalLight, intensity 0, pale blue, Movable
  - SkyLight — default
  - ShootingGallerySpotLight — SpotLight, intensity 200, white, Stationary
  - Plus 16× BP_LightFixtureWall_C and 9× BP_Torch_C blueprint light fixtures

  TestSpriteMap
  (/Game/NiagaraExamples/Utilities/SpriteGeneration/TestSpriteMap):
  - DirectionalLight — intensity 6, white, Movable
  - SkyLight — default

  If your actual gameplay level is NewMap, its lights aren't visible to me via
  this index — the World Partition external-actor packages aren't parsed for
  actor class. Want me to check the .umap contents another way (e.g. via the
  Unreal editor MCP tools), or is one of the two levels above actually the one
  you meant?

